Module kivakit.core.test
Package com.telenav.kivakit.core.test.random

Class RandomValueFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.telenav.kivakit.core.test.random.RandomValueFactory
  • public class RandomValueFactory
extends java.lang.Object
    Utility class for tests used to create random values. UnitTest has a variety of methods for random testing that use this class. Projects may subclass this to provide additional random values relevant to the project.

    Seeding

    The seed used for random values can be set with seed(long). KivaKit tests will emit a seed value when a test fails. This value can be fed to seed(long) to reproduce the failure.

    Values

    Values of the given types can be randomly produced:

    • Characters
    • Strings
    • Booleans
    • Bytes
    • Confidence
    • Count
    • Double
    • Identifier
    • Ints
    • Longs
    • Shorts
    • Unsigned Doubles
    • Unsigned Ints
    • Unsigned Longs
    Author:
    jonathanl (shibo)
    See Also:
    UnitTest
